The old Makupa causeway will be replaced by a 450m long Makupa bridge whose construction is set to be begin.The Makupa causeway is one of the three road links between the island and mainland. President Uhuru Kenyatta on Thursday morning commissioned the construction of the Sh4.5 billion Makupa Bridge that will offer a seamless flow of traffic in and out of Mombasa Island. 
The old Makupa causeway will be replaced by a 450m long Makupa bridge whose construction is set to be begin any time after a contract was signed between China Communications Construction Company Limited (CCCC) and the Kenya National Highways Authority (KeNHA).



