The Contract for the Construction of Makupa dual carriage Bridge was awarded by Kenha Director General Peter Mundinia to China Communications Construction Company Limited (CCCC) in November 2020.
The Makupa Causeway was built by the British colonial government in 1929 and is one of the links between Mombasa Island and the mainland, serving as the main road transport link between Mombasa Island and the Kenyan hinterland.





Speaking to residents of the area and project staff, President Kenyatta reiterated the Government's commitment to continue rolling out transformative development projects across the country.
Three road links
When complete in January 2022, the four-lane over-sea bridge, pave the way for its demolition and restoration of the ecosystem in the area; including free flow of water and marine life according to a statement from the State House’s twitter handle.
Makupa causeway is one of the three road links between the island and mainland, the others being Nyali bridge and Kipevu causeway.
The mainland linked by the causeway to the island is the region's industrial and transport hub.According to Kenha, the new bridge will bring into an end the aquatic life interference by the Makupa causeway a thing that has been a concern to marine experts.



